 this pun, which combines Pascal with scaltrezza (Ital., “sharp wit”) and treza (a Provençal word for “tressed stalks”), the French “pas” negates the “pensant” of the “roseau” in his famous phrase “man is a thinking reed.”

4 Katya: the ingénue in Turgenev’s “Fathers and Children.”

5 a trouvaille: a felicitous find.

6 Ada, who liked crossing orchids: she crosses here two French authors, Baudelaire and Chateaubriand.

